The Hawks arrested the trio on New Year&#8217;s Eve after they sold Umalusi senior certificates to an undercover police officer. JOHANNESBURG Three men accused of selling fake matric certificates in the Free State will remain behind bars until next week for a formal bail application. The Hawks arrested the trio on New Year s Eve after they sold Umalusi senior certificates to an undercover police officer at a shopping complex in Botshabelo.They appeared in court on Wednesday where the case was postponed. The Hawks Sifiso Nyakane says, The trio were nabbed in the act of selling fraudulent matric certificates. Investigations reveal that Mohale was previously convicted to five years and three years suspended for similar offence. 